【About Desire Value and Rationality Value】These
two values have the characteristic that when one
increases, the other decreases, and together they
function as a \C[17]Heart Meter\C[0].

When the Desire Value exceeds 70%, \C[17]Rain
enters Lust Mode\C[0], and both the meter and
Rain's eyes undergo a change. However, just
because the mode changes doesn't mean that
something will immediately happen. \C[17]This will
have a significant impact on the outcome of the
game.\C[0]

To deactivate the Lust Mode, you need to have a
Rationality Value of 50% or higher.

During the main scenario, there are scenes where
you will occasionally be prompted with Heart
Choices based on the Heart Meter. The range
indicated by the position of the cursor represents
Rain's emotional state, and the value on that side
of the range will increase.

Desire Value and Rationality Value can also be
increased or decreased through items and events
other than heart choices.

About the Status Gauge: In maps with battles, the
status gauge will be displayed.

When your HP reaches 0 in battle, one of the
following events will occur: Defeat Event, Sent
back to a specific location, or Game Over. Game
Over only occurs in certain event battles.

\C[17]TP\C[0] is a very important resource in this
game. In battles, it will mainly be consumed to
use powerful skills, so it's good to always be
aware of the remaining amount.

After the release of the Climax state, the Climax
Value returns to the Desire Value. The Desire
Value and Climax Value can increase or decrease in
various situations, but outside of battles, Rain
will never enter the Climax state.
